    "simplified": "损害赔偿（金）",
    "traditional": "損害賠償（金）",
    "definition": "Money awarded by a court to compensate someone for loss or injury caused by the unlawful act or negligence of another.",
    "legal_usage": "Damages are typically sought by plaintiffs in civil lawsuits. There are various types: compensatory damages (补偿性赔偿) reimburse actual losses (e.g., medical bills, lost wages); punitive damages (惩罚性赔偿) are intended to punish egregious wrongdoing and deter others; nominal damages (象征性赔偿) token amount when a wrong occurred but no substantial harm. California places certain limits on damages in specific cases (e.g., non-economic damages in medical malpractice). If a defendant is found liable, the court (or jury) will calculate damages based on evidence.",
