    "simplified": "辩护律师",
    "traditional": "辯護律師",
    "definition": "A lawyer who represents the defendant in a legal proceeding, responsible for defending their client's rights and interests. In criminal cases, also known simply as \"defense counsel.\"",
    "legal_usage": "A defense attorney may be privately hired or, if the defendant cannot afford one in a criminal case, provided by the government (e.g., a public defender). Their duties include advising the defendant, negotiating plea bargains, cross-examining prosecution witnesses, and presenting evidence and arguments in favor of the defendant. In California, defense attorneys must follow the California Rules of Professional Conduct, maintaining confidentiality and zealous advocacy. In civil cases, defense attorneys represent the party being sued and try to refute the plaintiff's claims.",
