    "mk": 8,
    "idi": 6,
    "simplified": "证据开示",
    "traditional": "證據開示",
    "definition": "The pre-trial process in which parties exchange relevant information, documents, and evidence to prepare for trial.",
    "legal_usage": "Discovery tools include depositions, interrogatories, requests for production of documents, requests for admissions, and subpoenas duces tecum. The process is governed by rules designed to prevent trial by ambush and promote fair resolution of disputes.",
