    "traditional": "離婚",
    "definition": "The legal dissolution of a marriage by a court or other competent body, terminating the marital relationship and determining issues of child custody, support, and property division.",
    "legal_usage": "To file for divorce in California (a no-fault divorce state), one doesn't need to prove wrongdoing; irreconcilable differences suffice. The divorce process includes resolving community property division, spousal support (alimony), child custody and support, and other matters. A divorce decree (judgment) is issued when finalized. California has a six-month residency requirement for filing and a six-month waiting period before a divorce can be finalized. Dissolution of marriage is another term for divorce. Uncontested divorces proceed by agreement, while contested ones may go to trial.",
