    "term": "Docket",
    "ipa": "ˈdɑːkɪt",
    "mk": 6,
    "idi": 3,
    "simplified": "案件登记表",
    "traditional": "案件登記表",
    "definition": "The official schedule of proceedings in court; a summary list of cases pending or actions taken in each case.",
    "legal_usage": "A court's docket is essentially its calendar or list of cases to be heard on a given day (court calendar), as well as the history of filings and orders in each case (case docket). For example, \"Your case is on the docket for next Monday.\" Attorneys check the docket to see hearing dates or what orders the judge has made. Many courts (including California state courts) have online docket systems where one can look up case summaries, upcoming appearances, or past orders. Marking something \"off-docket\" means removing it from the active calendar.",
