    "definition": "French for \\'on the bench.\\' When all judges of an appellate court hear a case together, rather than the usual panel of three.",
    "legal_usage": "En banc hearings are reserved for cases of exceptional importance or when a panel decision conflicts with prior circuit precedent. A party must petition for en banc rehearing after the initial panel decision. En banc decisions carry greater precedential weight.",
