    "traditional": "違章; 輕微違法",
    "definition": "A minor violation of law that is typically not punishable by imprisonment but rather by a fine or other penalty. It is the least serious category of offense, below misdemeanors.",
    "legal_usage": "Common infractions include most traffic tickets (speeding, parking violations) or municipal code violations. In California, infractions are not considered \"crimes\" technically, and one is not entitled to a jury trial or public defender for an infraction (unless upgraded). Penalties are usually fines or traffic school, without jail. If someone fails to address an infraction (like not paying a ticket or appearing), it can result in additional penalties or misdemeanor charges (e.g., failure to appear). Some offenses can be charged as an infraction or misdemeanor at prosecutorial discretion (e.g., certain municipal code violations).",
