    "definition": "The process of inquiring into a matter through gathering evidence, interviews, and examination, typically conducted by law enforcement or regulatory agencies to uncover facts about a crime or incident.",
    "legal_usage": "A police investigation precedes many criminal charges; detectives collect evidence, interview witnesses, and possibly conduct surveillance. Grand jury investigations might be conducted for widespread or political crimes. Defense attorneys also investigate to prepare their case, often hiring investigators to re- interview witnesses or find new evidence. In civil matters, parties may investigate each other's claims through discovery. An investigation can be formal (with subpoenas, search warrants) or informal. The quality of the initial investigation often affects the strength of the case at trial.",
