    "legal_usage": "As a concept, justice is the goal of the legal system ‒ ensuring fair outcomes and that the guilty are punished and the innocent are protected. In a courtroom context, \"Your Honor\" is used for trial judges, while appellate and supreme court judges are often called \"Justice \\[Last Name\\]\" (e.g., Justice Liu of the California Supreme Court). Phrases like \"obstructing justice\" refer to interfering with the legal process (as in obstruction of justice charges). Justice served means that a fair outcome was achieved. The Department of Justice (DOJ) is an executive agency for law enforcement.",
