    "traditional": "訴訟",
    "definition": "A legal action or proceeding in a civil court by which one party (plaintiff) sues another (defendant) for a remedy, such as damages or specific performance.",
    "legal_usage": "Filing a lawsuit begins with a complaint. Common types include personal injury lawsuits, contract disputes, and employment discrimination cases. The litigation process involves pleadings, discovery (exchange of evidence), possibly pre-trial motions, trial, and sometimes appeal. The term \"lawsuit\" is usually for civil matters, not criminal (one wouldn't call a criminal case a lawsuit). In California, superior courts handle civil lawsuits seeking more than \\$10,000 (unlimited jurisdiction) or up to \\$10,000 (limited jurisdiction, or small claims up to \\$5,000 for individuals). Many lawsuits settle before reaching trial.",
