    "legal_usage": "Litigation is often contrasted with alternative dispute resolution methods like mediation or arbitration. It involves filing pleadings (complaint, answer), discovery (exchanging evidence), pre-trial motions, and the trial itself. It can be lengthy and costly. One can refer to \"civil litigation\" meaning lawsuits in civil court. A \"litigator\" is an attorney who specializes in courtroom practice. Pending litigation means an ongoing case. After litigation concludes, enforcement of judgment may follow. The term can also be used generally: \"engaging in litigation\" means being involved in a lawsuit.",
