    "idi": 4,
    "simplified": "过失杀人",
    "traditional": "過失殺人",
    "definition": "The unlawful killing of another person without the malice aforethought (premeditation or specific intent to kill) that is required for murder. It is often divided into voluntary and involuntary categories.",
    "legal_usage": "Manslaughter in California includes: Voluntary manslaughter ‒ an intentional killing in the heat of passion or during a sudden quarrel without prior intent (e.g., catching one's spouse in adultery and killing in rage). Involuntary manslaughter ‒ an unintentional killing resulting from reckless or criminally negligent conduct (e.g., playing with a gun carelessly). Manslaughter is a lesser offense than murder and carries lighter penalties. For example, second-degree murder might be reduced to voluntary manslaughter if provocation is proven. There's also vehicular manslaughter for killings due to driving negligence or DUI.",
