    "legal_usage": "A property owner might sue a neighbor for private nuisance if, say, noxious fumes or loud noise from the neighbor's activities substantially interfere with the owner's enjoyment of their land. Public nuisance (e.g., polluting a river) can be addressed by government or class action. Nuisance cases often seek an injunction to stop the offending activity or damages for harm caused. For example, a factory emitting foul odors in a residential area may be deemed a nuisance by the court and ordered to mitigate or cease operations.",
