    "legal_usage": "In family law, a spouse may file a petition for nullity of marriage to have the marriage declared void from the start (e.g. due to fraud, bigamy, or incest). If granted, it's as if the marriage never existed legally. In California, nullity is sought on specific grounds like unsound mind, force, or physical incapacity. A nullity (annulment) affects marital status and can impact property division and spousal support rights, since legally no marriage occurred.",
