    "legal_usage": "Administering the oath is one of the first steps when a witness takes the stand. For example, before a witness gives testimony, a court clerk will ask the person to swear (or affirm) to tell the truth, \"so help you God.\" Failure to testify truthfully after taking an oath can lead to perjury charges. Jurors and public officials (e.g., during swearing-in ceremonies) also take oaths of office. An oath signifies the person's recognition of legal and moral duty to be truthful.",
