    "legal_usage": "During jury selection (voir dire), attorneys question members of the jury panel. The full panel might be, for example, 60 people called to court, from which 12 jurors and alternates will be picked. The term can also be used for a group of judges (e.g., a three-judge appellate panel). In interpreter contexts, \"panel\" often specifically implies jurors: \"Counsel, please address your questions to the panel.\" Some jurisdictions use \"venire\" to mean the panel of prospective jurors.",
